problem_statement.RootCause:
1) Incorrect assumption encoded in sphinx/ext/napoleon/docstring.py: GoogleDocstring._parse_other_parameters_section — it unconditionally calls self._format_fields(_('Other Parameters'), self._consume_fields()), thereby ignoring self._config.napoleon_use_param and forcing grouped/list formatting for the "Other parameters" section.

2) Existing correct decision pattern present in sphinx/ext/napoleon/docstring.py: GoogleDocstring._parse_parameters_section — it checks self._config.napoleon_use_param and uses:
   fields = self._consume_fields()
   if self._config.napoleon_use_param:
       return self._format_docutils_params(fields)
   else:
       return self._format_fields(_('Parameters'), fields)
   The mismatch between this method and _parse_other_parameters_section encodes the behavioral inconsistency.

3) Parsing helpers already provide the required relationship: _consume_fields supports multiple=True and NumpyDocstring._consume_field parses "name : type" (and comma-separated names) so that when multiple=True a declaration like "x, y : int" yields separate parameter tuples. This demonstrates the correct relationship that docutils-style param emission can be applied to "Other parameters" inputs.

4) The target formatting method for the napoleon_use_param=True behavior is sphinx/ext/napoleon/docstring.py: GoogleDocstring._format_docutils_params which emits lines using the exact patterns ':%s %s:' % (field_role, name) and ':%s %s: %s' % (type_role, name, type). The presence of this method shows the intended output when napoleon_use_param is True.

5) The hardcoded decision (always calling _format_fields in _parse_other_parameters_section) is the single-location encoding of the bug; no other hardcoded numeric constants are involved. The correct behavioral relationship is that the "Other parameters" section should follow the same napoleon_use_param decision as the "Parameters" section (i.e., when napoleon_use_param is True, produce docutils :param/:type output using fields produced by _consume_fields with multiple=True).
